  , issueCommentBody =
      "@soplakanets First of all a quick note that the auth key is not meant as a sole mean of protection for a RethinkDB server on the Internet (it's mostly meant for providing additional protection in internal networks).\r\n\r\nRegarding your specific case: You could use for example a Python script for automatically setting the auth key (e.g. run it on startup):\r\n```py\r\nimport rethinkdb as r\r\nconn = r.connect('localhost', 28015)\r\n\r\nr.db('rethinkdb').table('cluster_config').get('auth').update({'auth_key': 'secret key'}).run(conn)\r\n```"
  , issueCommentId = 75609255
